Silent to the Bone (2000) is a novel by E. L. Konigsburg for the "middle ages" or for young adults.[citation needed] It is a companion to The Outcasts of 19 Schuyler Place,a fifteen-years prequel published four years later.Acting as a best friend, therapist and detective, young Connor Kane with his adult half-sister "uncovers a complex, multilayered tale of human desires, adolescent confusion, and a touch of menace".Part detective story, some reviews portray it as mystery fiction primarily.It has been recommended for ages 10 to 14.